The next printed edition of any of the works of our author are the portions contained in Mabillon (5), who mentions no MS. by number but assigns the poetic works to a MS. formerly of Fleury, in his day in the collection of Queen Christina, and seen at Rome by the Bollandists. This again is Vat. Reg. 5557, formerly 1640. The same MS. is cited by Lebeuf (4), and Eugene de Certain (5) made the most complete investiga-

tion of it up to his time. In later catalogues and editions it is always Vat. Reg. 5557 which is cited.
